24/08/2005
CAPLJINA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- No concrete agreement on BiH police reform was reached during talks Tuesday (23 August) in Capljina, near Mostar, but senior BiH state and entity officials agreed to continue negotiations next week in Bjelasnica. BiH Security Minister Barisa Colak said he is optimistic that the stalemate would be resolved by the end of September. 
In other news, the International Commission on Missing Persons announced plans Tuesday to set up the country's first state-level Missing Persons Institute, with the help of the BiH Council of Ministers. It would merge current entity structures dealing with the problem. (Fena, PBS BiH - 23/08/05)
